RACE.RACE_TEXT: GREAT MEADOW RACE 1 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES PURSE $30,000. Hurdle, for Maidens, Three Years Old and Upward. Three-year-olds, 142 lbs.; four-year-olds, 150 lbs.; older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMPERIAL ASSASSIN (IRE) settled mid pack, ridden forward and headed the leader on the final turn, prevailed in long drive. QUICK MASTER took time to settle, bid on the final turn dueling with the leader, finished strong. REASSURED stalked in second, got shuffled back on the final turn, kept on doggedly to the wire. BOFFO KID led from the start, was challenged the final turn, dueled, then outfinished in the run to the wire. FRACING HOT settled in the rear, stayed well but outrun in stretch. MR JEFFERSON reserved, made a bid on the final turn to draw close, then weakened. FIELD MARSHAL fell at first hurdle.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked in second, shuffled back final turn, kept on to wire

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MERCOEUR (FR) stalked the pacesetter, assumed command surfacing from the lake, kept on strongly to prevail. STORM TEAM traveled reserved in the early going, made a strong bid two fences out, then outfinished in the stretch. SALAMANCA SCHOOL (FR) set the pace, was overtaken on the final turn, stayed on for third place. OUR FRIEND (IRE) got round the course and never threatened. FASHION LINE got round the course and never threatened. DON'T SHOUT (IRE) went off course and was pulled up.

Four-year-olds, 152 lbs.; older, 156 lbs. Non-winners in 2023, allowed 4 lbs.; in 2022-2023, 8 lbs. (Maiden claiming not considered in estimating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEOTROPIC ridden to lead after two hurdles, drew clear before the final hurdle, ridden out to the wire. PURE COURAGE rated nicely, closed willingly after the final hurdle for second. KIYOMORI traveled reserved, made a steady gain in the stretch to get up for third. FOR THE PARISH (IRE) traveled reserved, finished well but not trouble top three. RAMPOLDI PLAN traveled mid pack, finished well but not trouble top three. BARBADOS (IRE) trailed and had no rally. MASTER MCGRATH was on pace for the first circuit, then tired and dropped back.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GREAT MEADOW RACE 7 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES Hurdle Handicap, for Four Year Olds and Upward which are rated 115 or lower.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HE'LL DO rated, remained patient on the final turn, roused going into the final hurdle, got up for the win in deep stretch. PING PONG CHAMP stalked in second, rallied to hold a narrow lead at the final hurdle, then overtaken deep stretch and proved second best. SOUTH MOUNTAIN (IRE) traveled in a stalking position in third, rallied to a narrow lead on the final turn, sustained a drive to the last hurdle, then weakened in the stretch. STEP TO THE BAR trailed and finished tired. EYE OF GUNFIGHTER led, went off course approaching final turn when in the lead, and pulled up.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GREAT MEADOW RACE 8 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES PURSE $20,000. Hurdle, for Maidens, Three Years Old and Upward. Three-year-olds, 142 lbs.; four-year-olds, 150 lbs.; older, 154 lbs. Claiming price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AUCTION KINGDOM went unhurried early, commenced a steady gain on the second circuit to gain second at the final fence, was all out in the stretch for the win. GREYLOVER led stoutly, was challenged at the final fence and outfinished in stretch proving second best. BELLARMINE HALL traveled mid pack, produced a mild rally for third place. THE QUANTICO KID was ridden forward on the final circuit, in contention on the final turn, then weakened in the stretch. THALEEQ (GB) raced up with the pace till the final turn, then outrun thereafter. THE CHUNK was no threat and dropped back. LOVE SAGA settled towards the rear and had no rally. ICANDOTHAT trailed and lost contact with field on the final circuit. GO TAKE CHARGE had a poor jump on backside in first circuit, unseating the rider. GRUNION was no threat and pulled up.
